<reference xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" class="- topic/topic       reference/reference " ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" id="wzf1483522200237" xml:lang="en-us">
	<title class="- topic/title ">Access enable bit</title>
	<shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">The access enable bit for traps on accesses to activity monitor registers is required
		at EL2 and EL3.</shortdesc>
	<prolog class="- topic/prolog ">
		<permissions class="- topic/permissions " view="nonconfidential"/>
	</prolog>
	<refbody class="- topic/body        reference/refbody ">
		<section class="- topic/section ">
			<p class="- topic/p ">In the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> <term keyref="core">core</term>, the AMEN[4] bit in registers ACTLR_EL2 and ACTLR_EL3 controls the activity monitor registers enable.</p>
			<note class="- topic/note ">In the <ph class="- topic/ph "><keyword class="- topic/keyword "><tm class="- topic/tm " tmtype="reg">Cortex</tm></keyword><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">‑A76</keyword></ph> , the AMEN[4] bit is <term class="- topic/term " outputclass="archterm">RES0</term> in ACTLR and HACTLR. Activity monitors are not implemented in <term keyref="aarch32">AArch32</term>. </note>
			
		</section>
	</refbody>
</reference>
